This paper discusses the secure distribution of content in information-centric networking, which is a subfield of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also focuses on authentication and encryption, which are topics in computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses caching, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed protocol is also a lightweight authentication and key distribution protocol, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of symmetric key encryption, which is a topic in machine learning and cryptography (cs.DL).
